<HL>
   Raytheon's Beech Aircraft Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
05/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7A
</SO>
<CO>
   RTN
</CO>
<LP>
   LEXINGTON, Mass. -- Raytheon Co. said its Beech Aircraft
division has agreed to join with Pilatus Aircraft Ltd., of
Switzerland, to vie for a U.S. military contract for trainer
airplanes.
   Beech and Pilatus will propose a version of Pilatus's PC-9
turboprop trainer for selection in the Joint Primary Aircraft
Training System of the Navy and Air Force. Beech will be team
leader. The contract also includes simulators and training
systems.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The companies said that if Beech obtains a contract,
Pilatus will produce a significant portion of the planes,
with final assembly in Beech plants in Kansas.
</TEXT>
